# The mobile/ app is a separate Expo/React Native project (built via EAS or
# Xcode, never Vercel) — its own node_modules and generated native ios/android
# directories can balloon into tens of thousands of files (CocoaPods, vendored
# frameworks) that blow past Vercel's upload file-count limit. Vercel's CLI
# doesn't pick up mobile/.gitignore (nested), so this needs to be explicit here.
mobile/

# Agent worktrees: each one is a FULL checkout of this repo, node_modules and
# all, so a couple of them alone came to ~87k files — nearly six times Vercel's
# 15k cap, and the reason a deploy started failing with "files should NOT have
# more than 15000 items". Pure local tooling state; nothing here is ever served.
.claude/

# Scratch/agent config — small, but likewise not part of the deployment.
.agents/
